      "description": "Presenting a mechanically robust 996.2 Carrera powered by the 3.6L flat-six M96 engine. This example features a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a recent rear main seal (RMS) replacement, mitigating common failure points. The 6-speed G96 manual transaxle remains precise with no synchro grind, paired with a chassis that benefits from upgraded Bilstein dampers and refreshed control arm bushings. While the exterior shows honest patina, a recent bore-scope inspection confirms no scoring, and compression test results remain within factory tolerances. An excellent choice for the driver seeking peak flat-six performance and structural integrity.",
